      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A Process Reward Model (PRM) assigns a quality score to each intermediate reasoning step, not just to the final answer. This makes it possible to detect reasoning errors before they propagate to a wrong conclusion, guide search toward correct reasoning paths, and identify exactly which step in a chain-of-thought went wrong."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "ORM vs PRM: ORM scores only the final answer, PRM scores each individual reasoning step and can flag a bad step even when the final answer looks plausible"
        }
      },
