        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Outcome vs Process Supervision"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An Outcome Reward Model (ORM) evaluates only whether the final answer is correct. A PRM evaluates the reasoning quality at every step. For complex multi-step problems, a chain can produce a correct-looking answer through flawed reasoning, or an incorrect answer despite mostly correct reasoning. Only a PRM distinguishes these cases:"
          }
        ]
